/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `exprℝ -/
/-- A complex function is conformal if and only if the function is holomorphic or antiholomorphic
    with a nonvanishing differential. -/
theorem conformal_at_iff_differentiable_at_or_differentiable_at_comp_conj {f : exprℂ → exprℂ} {z : exprℂ} :
    conformal_at f z ↔
      (differentiable_at (exprℂ) f z ∨ differentiable_at (exprℂ) (f ∘ star_ring_end) ((star_ring_end) z)) ∧
        fderiv (exprℝ) f z ≠ 0 :=
  by
  rw [conformal_at_iff_is_conformal_map_fderiv]
  rw [is_conformal_map_iff_is_complex_or_conj_linear]
  apply and_congr_left
  intro h
  have h_diff := h.imp_symm fderiv_zero_of_not_differentiable_at
  apply or_congr
  · rw [differentiable_at_iff_restrict_scalars (exprℝ) h_diff]
  rw [← conj_conj z] at h_diff
  rw [differentiable_at_iff_restrict_scalars (exprℝ) (h_diff.comp _ conj_cle.differentiable_at)]
  refine' exists_congr fun g => rfl.congr _
  have : fderiv (exprℝ) (star_ring_end) ((star_ring_end) z) = _ := conj_cle.fderiv
  simp [fderiv.comp _ h_diff conj_cle.differentiable_at, this, conj_conj]
#align
  conformal_at_iff_differentiable_at_or_differentiable_at_comp_conj conformal_at_iff_differentiable_at_or_differentiable_at_comp_conj

/-- A real differentiable function of the complex plane into some complex normed space `E` is
    conformal at a point `z` if it is holomorphic at that point with a nonvanishing differential.
    This is a version of the Cauchy-Riemann equations. -/
theorem differentiable_at.conformal_at (h : differentiable_at (exprℂ) f z) (hf' : deriv f z ≠ 0) : conformal_at f z :=
  by
  rw [conformal_at_iff_is_conformal_map_fderiv, (h.has_fderiv_at.restrict_scalars (exprℝ)).fderiv]
  apply is_conformal_map_complex_linear
  simpa only [ne.def, ext_ring_iff]
#align differentiable_at.conformal_at differentiable_at.conformal_at

/-- If a complex function `e` is differentiable at a real point, then its restriction to `ℝ` is

theorem has_deriv_at.comp_of_real (hf : has_deriv_at e e' ↑z) : has_deriv_at (fun y : exprℝ => e ↑y) e' z := by
  simpa only [of_real_clm_apply, of_real_one, mul_one] using hf.comp z of_real_clm.has_deriv_at
